  "local_port": 54162,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "In this WordPress era, why do people still study coding instead of just using it?",
  "response": "While WordPress and similar platforms have made it easier for people to create websites without deep technical knowledge, there are several reasons why people still study coding:\n\n1. **Customization**: WordPress and other CMS platforms offer a lot of flexibility, but they have limitations. To create highly customized websites or functionalities that go beyond the available plugins and themes, coding knowledge is essential.\n\n2. **Performance Optimization**: Coders can optimize websites for speed and efficiency, which is crucial for user experience and SEO. Understanding the underlying code allows for more precise optimizations than what generic plugins can offer.\n\n3. **Security**: A deep understanding of coding helps in identifying and fixing security vulnerabilities. Custom code can be more secure than relying on third-party plugins, which can be targets for hackers.\n\n4. **Career Opportunities**: Proficiency in coding opens up a wide range of job opportunities in web development, software engineering, and other tech fields. These skills are highly valued in the job market.\n\n5. **Problem-Solving Skills**: Coding teaches logical thinking and problem-solving, which are valuable skills in many areas beyond just building websites.\n\n6. **Understanding Technology**: Studying coding helps people understand how technology works, making them more informed users and creators of digital content.\n\n7. **Independence**: Knowing how to code means you are not reliant on pre-built solutions. You can create your own tools, fix issues without waiting for updates, and have full control over your projects.\n\n8. **Innovation**: Coders can innovate and create new technologies, applications, and solutions that don't yet exist. This drives technological advancement and can lead to the development of groundbreaking products and services.\n\n9. **Learning Mindset**: The tech industry evolves rapidly. Studying coding fosters a continuous learning mindset, helping people stay updated with the latest technologies and trends.\n\n10. **Community and Collaboration**: Being part of the coding community allows for collaboration, sharing of knowledge, and contributing to open-source projects, which can be personally and professionally rewarding.\n\nIn summary, while tools like WordPress have democratized web development, coding skills remain essential for those who want to push boundaries, ensure security, optimize performance, and build a career in technology.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
